                        <interp inst="t18471213-name-240" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS MIDDLETON</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City policeman</hi>, 452.) On 30th Nov., about half-past two o'clock in the afternoon, I was in Upper Thames-street—I saw the prisoner with another boy—I followed them—they closed up to Mr. Ray, tried his right pocket and then his left, the prisoner's companion drew out this handkerchief and gave it to the prisoner—I ran and got it from his hand—I called, "Stop thief"—Ray turned round—I asked him if it was his handkerchief—he said, "Yes"—the other boy escaped.</p>
